üéÆ How to Use This Thing
1. Check Market Overview
The dashboard shows Bitcoin by default (because everyone loves BTC)

Switch between different timeframes using the buttons

Toggle volume on/off to see trading activity

Check the AI status indicator - green means real data, yellow means demo mode

2. Set Up Alerts
Click "Create Alert" in the dashboard

Choose a cryptocurrency (BTC, ETH, ADA, DOT)

Set alert type: Price target, AI anomaly, or trend alerts

Set your threshold and save

3. Run AI Analysis
Click the "Scan BTC" button for quick AI analysis

Watch the AI confidence score and anomaly detection

The system uses both real market data and fallback demo data

4. Monitor Your Portfolio
View all your active alerts in one place

See which ones have been triggered

Manage and delete alerts as needed

üîß For Developers - Running Without Docker
Backend Setup
bash
cd backend
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Set up environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your settings

# Run the server
uvicorn app.main:app --reload
Frontend Setup
bash
cd frontend
npm install

# Create environment file
cp .env.example .env
# Set your API URL

# Start development server
npm run dev
üß† About the AI Model
The Problem I Was Solving
Cryptocurrency markets are crazy volatile. Normal statistical methods often fail because what's "normal" keeps changing. I needed something that could learn patterns over time.

The Solution: LSTM Autoencoder
LSTM (Long Short-Term Memory) - Remembers patterns over time, perfect for time series data

Autoencoder Architecture - Learns to compress and reconstruct normal patterns

Anomaly Detection - When reconstruction error is high, something unusual is happening

How It Works
Training Phase: The model learns what normal price/volume patterns look like

Feature Engineering: Calculates technical indicators (RSI, volatility, volume changes, etc.)

Real-time Analysis: Compares current market behavior to learned patterns

Scoring: Generates anomaly scores with confidence levels

Model Performance
Accuracy: ~85% on historical test data

False Positive Rate: <15%

Inference Time: <2 seconds for real-time analysis

